Exercise 1: Inventory Management System
Scenario: 
You are developing an inventory management system for a warehouse. Efficient data storage and retrieval are crucial.

Why Data Structures and Algorithms are Essential

In an inventory management system, a warehouse may contain thousands or even millions of products. Efficient data structures and algorithms help in:

-->Fast storage and retrieval of product information.
-->Quick updates to inventory quantities and prices.
-->Reduced memory usage.
-->Improved system performance when handling large datasets.
-->Faster search, insertion, and deletion operations.

Without proper data structures and algorithms, inventory operations would become slow and inefficient as the number of products increases.

Suitable Data Structures

Some suitable data structures for inventory management are:

Data Structure	Usage
-->ArrayList	Stores products sequentially and allows easy iteration.
-->HashMap	Stores products using productId as the key for fast access.
-->LinkedList	Useful when frequent insertions and deletions are required.
-->TreeMap	Maintains products in sorted order.

For this system, HashMap is the best choice because it provides fast access, insertion, update, and deletion using the productId.


