Analysis
Time Complexity

Using HashMap:

Operation	Time Complexity
Add Product	O(1)
Update Product	O(1)
Delete Product	O(1)
Search Product	O(1)

Explanation:

HashMap stores data using key-value pairs.
The productId acts as the key.
Hashing allows direct access to product records without searching through all products.


Optimization Techniques
Use HashMap
Provides constant-time operations for add, update, delete, and search.
Use Unique Product IDs
Prevents duplicate entries and improves retrieval efficiency.
Efficient Hash Functions
Reduces collisions and maintains O(1) performance.
Database Indexing
If inventory data is stored in a database, indexing productId improves search speed.
Caching Frequently Accessed Products
Reduces repeated database access and improves performance.
Conclusion

An Inventory Management System can be efficiently implemented using a HashMap because it provides O(1) average time complexity for insertion, update, deletion, and search operations. Proper selection of data structures and algorithms ensures better performance, scalability, and efficient management of large inventories.
